lign=left class=m><span class=title>   Terror is a Piece of Cake....</span><hr size=1> ...if you have the right number and mix of people and a solid tactic that works.<br>
<br>
Would anyone mind sharing their success stories on how to take out this beastly golem?  On our Fear raid Sunday, we got him down to around 40 percent (some said less) before we succumbed to his charms...heh heh.  I thought we did well on our guild's very first attempt.<br>
<br>
I had 35 folks...ranging from 47 to 55.  Two 55+ enchanters and a 47 enchanter.  Three clerics.  The rest of the mix had the usually smattering of other classes.  We put the tanks out front away from the casters...and parked pets right behind the tanks.  We wimpy types parked ourselves on a hill behind the rest of the force.<br>
<br>
I noticed we had more company than the usual 2 amy's and their pets.  I know I saw a gorgon...and not sure what else.  But we lasted for a good five minutes maybe more before dying.  I managed to get my CR up to 144.  But I know some raiders did NOT bring CR gear.<br>
<br>
I've seen a couple of successful Terror take-downs, and would really appreciate the insight.  Thanks in advance. <p>Selilya Withertouch<BR>
Winnower of the Violent Harvest <BR>
Devoted Daughter of Innoruuk <BR>
<BR>
<center><img src="http://members.aol.com/selilya/selilya.jpg"  border=0> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utorquill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torquill</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/images/icons/Eeeeek_Face_2.gif HEIGHT =15 WIDTH=15 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 190<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/13/01 11:58:34 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.flspot.com/loa/mb/icons/ico_torquill.gif Height=84 Width=75></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Terror is a Piece of Cake....</span><hr size=1> Hiya Selilya<br>
The last Fear I was on we treated Terror like any other mob...and got our butts handed to us.<br>
We then gathered (while waiting for rezes <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) as much CR gear as we could get. Once everyone was back and GTG we did Terror just like Vox. Two waves of tanks with casters waiting for 50% to nuke. I think we had about 4-6 deaths that time.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uganonstormwynd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ganon Stormwynd</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.angelfire.com/il/selectevil/icons/Icon_Fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=BEBEBE>Ganon the Pathfinder</font><br><font color=red>Brell BoTB Winner</font></span><br>  Posts: 304<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/13/01 12:14:29 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http:\\www.righteousfire.com/images/gano1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Terror is a Piece of Cake....</span><hr size=1> Treat him like Vox and you'll win.  Lots of cold resist gear, keep casters out of the AE until it's necessary to bring them in.  Having jboots or an instant click item set in your first buff spot is extremely helpful in keeping necessary hp and resist buffs on people as well.<br>
 <p>Ganon the Pathfinder <BR>
Guild Leader<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.silentredemption.org/" TARGET="_new"><IMG ALT="Silent Redemption Member" BORDER=0 SRC="http://fairblade.sinbad.net/images/SRlogo.gif"></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrungleeisenguss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krungle Eisenguss</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 227<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/13/01 12:22:30 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/beertr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Terror is a Piece of Cake....</span><hr size=1> I lost about 6 buffs at the beginning of that fight. WTF dispelled me? Was it Terror? Or the Gorgan?<br>
 <br>
Also, how do you control the extra MoBs? Do you try to send out a Ranger or Druid to peel them off on the pull and kite them around? Do you attempt to get an Enchanter up in Terror's AE range to mez them? If the latter is true, WTF dispelled me and how would that effect a mez?<br>
<br>
 <p><center><img src="http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglesig.jpg" border=0></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot <img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/goldstartr.gif align=middle></span><br>  Posts: 1129<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/13/01 1:17:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Terror is a Piece of Cake....</span><hr size=1> Terror's AE dispells just like Vox's AE dispells.   Have a right click buff in your first slot as Ganon said.  Either Jboots, Goblin earring, or any other item that is an instant click effect with a buff icon.   The instant you get debuffed click your jboots again putting that buff up.  Sometimes the AE will skip the first icon but generally I can keep every buff up during a fight.  If you have 2 right clicks have both on the top and spam both of them when you get hit and you should never lose a buff.  If you have a bard in the group put his songs right after your instant clicks. <br>
<br>
To kill Terror just treat him like a stronger Vox, thats all he really is.<br>
<br>
As for getting him solo thats up to the pull team to be able to peel him off.  Since I've not been on pull I can't really help on how to do that.  <p><table>
