<br>
alot has been covered, but...<br>
<br>
-180+ cold resists<br>
-solid group makeup(you need enough healers/tanks)<br>
-Tanks need to be aware that he hits for 490? back out when you start getting hit<br>
-right-click item as your top buff(if he debuffs you, you're going to start dieing fast)<br>
-even thought you have a right click up top, sometimes you lose your 2-4th buff for some reason, stick junk buffs there, keep HP/ac/resist buffs in the 8th+ slots.<br>
-put lower level people, or people who neglected getting resist gear with bards<br>
-keep casters that are out of mana or can't hurt him out of the fight so they don't waste healers mana.<br>
-Pull him solo, that means kiting him around and killing his 2 amy knights while someone is kiting him(make sure the GY is totally clear before you do terror)<br>
<br>
That's all I can think of atm, if you have any questions I could answer them.<br>
<br>
